qas.question: Where are the French Prealps located?
What mountains are located in Switzerland and France?
What follows the watershed from the Mediterranean Sea to the Wienerwald?

answers.text: The secondary chain of the Alps

qas.question: What heads approximately east-northeast once at the Swiss bored?

answers.text: the line of the main chain

context: Series of lower mountain ranges run parallel to the main chain of the Alps, including the French Prealps in <a0_0>France<a0_0/> and <a1_0>the Jura Mountains<a1_0/> in Switzerland and France. <a2_0>The secondary chain of the Alps<a2_0/> follows the watershed from the Mediterranean Sea to the Wienerwald, passing over many of the highest and most well-known peaks in the Alps. From the Colle di Cadibona to Col de Tende it runs westwards, before turning to the northwest and then, near the Colle della Maddalena, to the north. Upon reaching the Swiss border, <a3_0>the line of the main chain<a3_0/> heads approximately east-northeast, a heading it follows until its end near Vienna.
